<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900608-0052</DOCNO><DOCID>900608-0052.</DOCID><HL>   Technology Brief -- Calgene Inc.:   Quarterly Charge Planned   From Layoffs, Consolidation</HL><DATE>06/08/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   CGNE</CO><IN>MEDICAL AND BIOTECHNOLOGY (MTC)</IN><LP>   Calgene Inc., an agricultural biotechnology concern basedin Davis, Calif., said it will incur a &quot;significant&quot; one-timecharge in its third quarter ending June 30, citing layoffsand severance payments, and a greenhouse closure inconsolidating sites.   A spokesman said an estimate of the charge wasn'tavailable. In the year-earlier quarter, Calgene had a netloss of $1.7 million, on revenue of $8.1 million.</LP><TEXT>   Calgene also said that this year, it will change its Sept.30 fiscal year end to June 30, a time of seasonally lowactivity in agriculture, when accounting relating toinventory and other factors is easier and less expensive thanin September.   Calgene said it has stopped development programs ingenetic engineering of certain plant hybrids and of alfalfa,and laid off 35 employees, or about 11% of the total workforce, from those programs last week. These moves and theclosure of one of Calgene's three greenhouse operations areaimed at focusing the company on its core projects of oilsmodification, development of cotton that isn't damaged byherbicide, and creation of improved-quality tomatos. Calgenesaid the actions will reduce expenses by at least $3 millionannually.</TEXT></DOC>